The C89 library can now be built under Linux, Cygwin or Windows.

Currently, two different versions of the libarary are build - one for the old
memory model (16 Mb code space, 32Kb data, heap and stack space), and one for 
the new 'large' memory model (16mb code, data and heap space, 32kb stack space).

See the individual platform NOTES files for details.


